<br>
I remember the blood rushing to my head.  The thudding of my heart as I leaned over and covered her lips with my own.  They were soft, warm and trembled as I’m sure mine must have.  I had the courage only to place the merest touch of my lips to hers before I drew back.  But she had opened her eyes to stare into mine and she breathed a single word… “More.” And I was lost.<br>
<br>
I closed my eyes, as the memories exploded vividly in my mind and my heart.  I had pulled her into my arms then, and we kissed.  Exploring and tasting until we both shook with desire.  Then I held her until both our hearts were calm again, and wrapping her close to me in my cloak, we were content to lay down and sleep.<br>
